Package org.jsweet.transpiler.extension

Class Java2TypeScriptAdapter

java.lang.Object
org.jsweet.transpiler.extension.PrinterAdapter
org.jsweet.transpiler.extension.Java2TypeScriptAdapter
Direct Known Subclasses:
RemoveJavaDependenciesAdapter
public class Java2TypeScriptAdapter extends PrinterAdapter
This is an adapter for the TypeScript code generator. It overrides the default adapter's behavior.
Author:
Renaud Pawlak

  • Method Details

    • getPrinter

      public Java2TypeScriptTranslator getPrinter()
      Description copied from class: PrinterAdapter
      Gets the printer on which rely the adapter (this is not recommended).

      Accessing the printer with this method allows the user to access the internal javac API directly (com.sun.tools.javac), which is non-standard and may get deprecated in future Java versions. As a consequence, to write sustainable adapters, it is not recommended to use the printer API.

      Instead, use the adapter's API directly, which relies on an abstraction of the AST: javax.lang.model and org.jsweet.transpiler.model. If some feature seems to be missing, please contact JSweet.org to help improving this API.

      Overrides:
      getPrinter in class PrinterAdapter

    • substituteExtends

      public boolean substituteExtends​(TypeElement type)
      Description copied from class: PrinterAdapter
      Manually substitutes the super class of a given type.

      This method should print " extends X" and return true to force the substitution of the extends clause of a given class. This is a low-level operation and it is not encouraged to use it except for very specific contexts.

      Overrides:
      substituteExtends in class PrinterAdapter
